# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Indian Kitchen Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed @vercel/analytics Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 to project dependencies
- Used npm (project's package manager) to install the package
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json accordingly

### 2. Updated Root Layout File
**File**: `src/app/layout.tsx`

- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body tag, after all other components
- Followed the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects

### 3. Implementation Details
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.9 with App Router
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Installation Method**: Followed the latest official Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide
- **Component Placement**: Added at the end of the body in the root layout, ensuring it loads on all pages

### 4. Verification Steps Completed
✅ Build verification: Project builds successfully with no errors
✅ Linter check: No new linting errors introduced (existing unrelated errors in HomeFounderNote.tsx remain)
✅ TypeScript compilation: Passes without errors
✅ Lock file updated: package-lock.json updated with new dependency

## How It Works
The Analytics component will automatically track page views and user interactions once the application is deployed to Vercel. The component is lightweight and will not impact page performance.

## Next Steps
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. After deployment, analytics data will start appearing in the Vercel dashboard

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and dependencies
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component

## Notes
- The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation exactly as requested
- No breaking changes to existing functionality
- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body to ensure it doesn't block page rendering
- All existing components and functionality remain unchanged
